author: @Mayur7Garg
text: Great video but I dislike the fact that the video never addresses comparative improvement in performance had there been no AI model to help. Like I understand AI helped kids be better, but I wanted to know how much these kids would have improved in absence of AI and just by sheer practice and conventional training. Simply put, this is a great problem to solve but can you quantitatively say that AI was needed?
